State ex rel. Union Free High School District of the City of Crandon, etc., Respondent, vs. Robbins, Town Clerk, Appellant. October 11 November 8, 1922.

State ex rel. Union Free High School Dist. v. Chaney, ante, p. 585, followed.

For the appellant the cause was submitted on the brief of Eastman & Goldman of Marinette. For the respondent there was a brief by John F. Hooper of Crandon and Eberlein & Larson of Shawano, and oral argument by Mr-. Albert S. Larson and Mr. Hooper. Vinje, C. J.

This case is identical in its facts so far as the appeal is concerned with that of State ex rel. Union Free High School District v. Chaney, decided herewith (ante, p. 585, 190 N. W. 353), and is governed by that decision.

By the Court.- — Order affirmed.
